title: For Sale:  COLT 1903 Pocket Hammerless.32 Auto, TYPE 1, Mfd 1908...BEAUTIFULLY ENGRAVED
postcontent: Here's a beautiful little Colt pistol! This is an early Colt Model 1903 .32 Pocket Hammerless.this pistol has several early features including the longer 4" barrel and the seperate barrel bushing. This handsome gun is elaborately engraved in a lovely floral scroll pattern and has gold wire inlay on both sides of the frame and slide. The top of the slide also has what appears to be the U.S. Presidential Seal engraved and filled with gold wash. The engraving is not factory original but is perfectly executed and easily equal to that of a factory engraved gun. The grips are ivory with flush Colt gold medallions. Overall condition is extremely nice and the pistol retains almost 100% of the blue finish (there are only a very few light handling marks keeping it from being perfect). The mechanics appear to be in perfect working order. The bore is the only weak point as it is frosted throughout, apparently put away without proper cleaning. The serial number places production in about 1908. Overall, a great gun and an exceptionally handsome pistol!
